//axhob_operation
{rbtgo_ark_enshrine}

NOTE: This operation enshrines upstream base images into
{gar_service}
as content-addressed, human-readable anchors.
The
{rbtr_director}
submits a Cloud Build job that copies each declared
{rbrv_image_origin}
from its upstream registry to GAR with an anchor tag using
the reliquary skopeo image
(`skopeo copy --all`), preserving the manifest list and all per-platform manifests for multi-platform images.
The anchor results are returned via `buildStepOutputs` and
{rbrv_image_anchor}
is then written back to the vessel regime locally.

NOTE: Enshrine is a pre-build preparation step.
It must be run before
{rbtgo_ark_conjure}
when anchored base images are desired.
Conjure works without anchors (passing ORIGIN through), but anchored images provide reproducibility and air-gap readiness.

NOTE: Enshrine runs on Cloud Build, not the Director's workstation.
No local skopeo installation is required.
The GCB step uses Mason SA ambient credentials via the metadata server for GAR writes.

The enshrine operation:

//axhopt_typed_parameter
{rbrv_sigil}
. *Validate Input Parameters*:
.. {rbbc_require}
vessel provided as first argument
.. {rbbc_require}
vessel contains at least one
{rbrv_image_origin}
declaration (slots 1-3)

//axhos_step
. *Submit Enshrine Cloud Build Job*:
.. Compose `builds.create` JSON with:
... Single step using
the reliquary skopeo image
as the builder image (script: `rbgje01-enshrine-copy.sh`)
... `_RBGE_*` substitutions: `_RBGE_GAR_HOST`, `_RBGE_GAR_PATH`, `_RBGE_IMAGE_n_ORIGIN` (n = 1, 2, 3; empty for unused slots). Base images are stored in the shared `enshrine` namespace (`{repo}/enshrine:{anchor}`), not per-vessel.
... Mason SA, private pool, timeout
.. Submit via `builds.create` and wait for completion
.. The GCB step, for each non-empty ORIGIN slot:
... Inspects upstream image to obtain the manifest digest
... {rbbc_store}
`<<DIGEST>>` -- the sha256 digest of the upstream manifest (manifest list digest for multi-platform images, single manifest digest for single-platform images)
... Constructs anchor: sanitize origin tag (`:` `/` replaced with `-`), append first 10 hex chars of sha256 digest
... Example: `python:3.11-slim` with `sha256:abc123def4...` produces `python-3.11-slim-abc123def4`
... Copies upstream image to the shared `enshrine` namespace in GAR (`{repo}/enshrine:{anchor}`) using `skopeo copy --all`, transferring the manifest list and all per-platform manifests atomically. The anchor is vessel-independent — multiple vessels sharing the same base image origin share one enshrined artifact.
... {rbbc_require}
copy succeeds -- the anchor tag is now a permanent, content-addressed reference in
{gar_service}
containing all upstream platforms
... Single-platform upstream images are handled identically -- `skopeo copy --all` is a no-op on the platform dimension when only one platform exists
.. Writes JSON anchor results to `/builder/outputs/output` (returned as `buildStepOutputs`)

//axhos_step
. *Extract Anchors and Write Regime*:
.. Read `buildStepOutputs[0]` from the completed build result (base64-decoded JSON)
.. For each slot present in the result:
... Write anchor string to `RBRV_IMAGE_n_ANCHOR` in the vessel's `rbrv.env`

//axhoot_typed_output
{rbrv_image_anchor}
Per-slot anchor string written to the vessel regime.

//axhoc_completion
Successful execution produces anchored base image references in
{gar_service}
(with all upstream platforms preserved) and updates the vessel regime with
{rbrv_image_anchor}
values.
The vessel is now ready for reproducible
{rbtgo_ark_conjure}
builds using GAR-mirrored base images.
Multi-platform conjure vessels pull the correct platform from the anchored manifest list automatically.
Re-running enshrine with the same
{rbrv_image_origin}
but a different upstream digest produces a new anchor (upstream image was updated).
Re-running with the same digest is idempotent.

=== {rbtgo_ark_conjure}

Conjures an
{rbtga_ark_image}
by building a container image
({rbtgog_ark})
from a vessel specification.
Build context delivered via pouch (FROM SCRATCH OCI image in GAR), submitted via `builds.create` API. The combined job produces both `-image` and `-about` (about steps embedded via stitch). Vouch is a separate Cloud Build job using DSSE envelope signature verification.

include::RBSAC-ark_conjure.adoc[]

[[rbtgo_ark_enshrine]]
//axvo_method axd_transient axd_grouped
=== {rbtgo_ark_enshrine}

Enshrines upstream base images into
{gar_service}
({rbtgog_ark}),
producing content-addressed
{rbrv_image_anchor}
references from
{rbrv_image_origin}
declarations.
The
{rbtr_director}
pulls each upstream image by tag, pushes to GAR with a human-readable anchor tag, and writes the anchor back to the vessel regime.

include::RBSAE-ark_enshrine.adoc[]

[[rbtgo_ark_graft]]
//axvo_method axd_transient axd_grouped
=== {rbtgo_ark_graft}

Grafts a locally-built container image into the
{rbtgi_repository}
({rbtgog_ark})
via native docker/podman push.
The image push itself is local (no Cloud Build); about and vouch follow as Cloud Build jobs.

include::RBSAG-ark_graft.adoc[]

